=m><span class=title> Possible Dragon Loot changes...</span><hr size=1> As I said in an earier post, I have been pondering a few changes in the loot/lotto for our dragon raids.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Vox<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  White scale</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bards, Priest, and Casters only<br>-Bards <br>Epic Piece.<br>-Priests and Casters<br>Nice wis/int plus cold resist= longer life span on our raids as well as more mana for nukes and heals.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Staff of Forbidden Rites </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>All Random<br>-Although it is cleric, shaman, druid, pally, the 10 charges of resurrect can be used by ANY class.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Nagafen<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Red Scale</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bards and Warriors only<br>-Epic piece for both classes. There is nicer armor out there now than the red scale bp.<br><br>What are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  your</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> thoughts?<br><br>I want to avoid those who would double dip and keep the true spirit of the KCoG alive. I feel these changes would benefit those who have been long time supporters of the KCoG. <p><br><br><center><img src="http://www.coastnet.com/~drake/EQ/Sigs/newsig.jpg"></center> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uladyazureskye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LadyAzureSkye</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/1/02 6:26:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utortoiseeldersquirtle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TortoiseEldersquirtle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/1/02 8:09:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible Dragon Loot changes...</span><hr size=1> Being a Paladin with a Red Draggie BP and not interested in the White Scale, I say...<br><br>Vox<br>White scale<br>Bards, Priest, and Casters only<br>-Bards <br>Epic Piece.<br>-Priests and Casters<br>Nice wis/int plus cold resist= longer life span on our raids as well as more mana for nukes and heals.<br><br>Nagafen<br>Red Scale<br>Bards and Warriors only<br>-Epic piece for both classes. There is nicer armor out there now than the red scale bp.<br><br><br>Well, the +10 mr/fr would help on a KCG Nagafen raid...<br>And you might hear some melee complaint if priests can loot the scale they can use, and the melee cannot.<br>However, bards prefer to help their chances for an epic, but epics only lead to a person passing 52 and not helping KCG, I really doubt a person goes &quot;wewt, got my old world cloak/BP, time to level to 53&quot; whereas your Bard or Warrior will. In the end it would help KCG (Though very minimally) to have a chance at someone making a cloak or BP and living through one more AE rather then having a 53+ Bard or Warrior make clearing to Vox or Naggy that much easier (As much as I liked the hour it saved last Vox <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br><br>As for the Staff... fantastic idea if it's clickable from inventory. No way in hell I'm going to melee with a 25/50 and clerics and druids and shaman shouldn't be meleeing at all.<br><br>Summary:<br>White Scale change: Priests/Casters and Bards only<br>Red Scale change: Melee, Hybrid, and Bard only<br>Staff change: Everyone<br><br>Did I just make an intelligent and insightful post? Jesus. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utortoiseeldersquirtle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TortoiseEldersquirtle</A> at: 6/1/02 8:14:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useisekerrswiftstrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seisekerr Swiftstrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/1/02 8:22:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible Dragon Loot changes...</span><hr size=1> I agree with everyone Azure posted.<br><br>Everyone else who wins the scale will just sell it. Also, I was the one who brought up the staff idea with you at the last vox raid. The staff is right clickable from inventory and I believe it should be an &quot;all roll&quot; item, because the ressurections are nice and its 2hb if i remember right -- what healers do you see wielding a 2hb with about only 10wis on it(whereas a shield + weapon = more), that doesnt have a right click DD or some special situational proc on it? <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84680">Seisekerr Swiftstrike</a> -- Master of the Celestial Fists<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102119">Avante Twi`Zweiswordze</a> -- Troubadour of the Wind<br><i>Karana Server</i><br><img src=http://seisekerr.freewebspace.com/thunderkick.gif><br><img src=http://seisekerr.freewebspace.com/trunks2.gif></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KCoG Founder</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/1/02 11:46:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwinclients.com/sd/haemish_new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible Dragon Loot changes...</span><hr size=1> I'm ok with all the changes listed. <br><br>The Red Dragonscale BP and White DragonScale cloak can be beaten with other gear. However, they are the only sources for an epic piece, and though I'm not a fan of the epic quests, a lot of folks want them. I daresay that a lot of &quot;double-dipping&quot; and people staying under 53 is because of the epic quests. I never liked that at all. <br><br>When I first set the Staff as users of it only, I wasn't aware the 10 charges of Rez could be used by anyone. Now that I know it can be, I'd be fine with it being an all/all item. I'd have loved it as a warrior. <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>Founder<Br>Karana Council of Guilds<br>"I don't play role-playing games to be a politician."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzizzerzazzerzuz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zizzerzazzerzuz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/2/02 1:47:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible Dragon Loot changes...</span><hr size=1> sounds good to me<br><br>i would much rather see items going to those who can use it for what they need, then those who would sell it for something they need, forcing someone that was on the 